The off-duty policeman killed his girlfriend and her mother in Site C. CAPE TOWN - Cape Town police are investigating a double murder and suicide after a police constable killed his girlfriend and her mother before turning the gun on himself.The incident occurred in Khayelitsha earlier this week.Constable Thembile Gwegwe is believed to have gone to his girlfriend's house in Site C where he shot and killed her 50-year-old mother.The off-duty policeman then allegedly shot dead his 28-year-old girlfriend.Residents called the police and paramedics shortly after the incident.Cape Town police have opened a murder case and an inquest into the matter for further investigation.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)